node.title: New York City Opening Safe Sites for Narcotics Use After Setting Overdose Record in 2020
node.description: There were more than 2,060 overdoses in New York City during 2020. The CDC estimated the U.S. had more than 93,000 overdoses last year, up 30 percent from 2019.

node.title: 'Are you OK?': Ruben lost his dad to suicide at age 14, now he helps others in need
node.description: As a teenager, Ruben was heartbroken and struggled to understand why his father took his own life. Eleven years later, he now volunteers as a phone counsellor at Lifeline to help save the lives of others.

node.title: Vaccination mandate won't prevent crisis in childcare with early educators 'leaving in droves', advocate warns
node.description: Queensland childcare advocate Georgie Dent says she is concerned the sector will lose significant numbers of staff next year, despite the vaccination mandate for educators.

node.title: Most big employers say they are mandating COVID-19 vaccines
node.description: Yet support for vaccine mandates could wane if a court strikes down contested OSHA rule requiring shots or testing.

node.title: Regeneron says its antibody treatment may not be as effective against Omicron, but testing is underway.
node.description: The company said that analyses and modeling of mutations in the variant suggest that they may weaken the effect of the treatment, but that studies using Omicron’s full sequences are incomplete.

node.title: Janet Yellen still supports a plan to make banks give the I.R.S. new customer data.
node.description: “I think it’s important that the I.R.S. have visibility into opaque income streams,” the Treasury secretary said.

node.title: Federal health officials say that they are expanding the search for Omicron in the U.S.
node.description: The Centers for Disease Control and Prevention was “actively looking” for the variant but had not found a case so far.

node.title: El Chapo’s Wife Sentenced to 3 Years in Prison
node.description: Emma Coronel Aispuro pleaded guilty in June to helping her husband, Joaquin Guzmán Loera, smuggle drugs into the United States and escape from prison.

node.title: Suu Kyi Has Sixth Corruption Charge Issued By Myanmar Government, Trial Verdict Postponed
node.description: The sixth corruption charge Tuesday involves former President Win Myint, plus a new witness is now allowed to testify, which delayed the trial verdict.

node.title: Grinch Actor Charms Internet by Complimenting Woman's Contour in Viral Video
node.description: "I'm so glad I opened the comments and [found] that I'm not the only one who found this weirdly attractive," one commenter said.

node.title: Salmon producers develop alliance to help tackle 'negative' press
node.description: Tasmania's salmon industry has weathered years of criticism, most recently from Booker-prize winning author Richard Flanagan. Now it's enlisting business leaders to fight back.

node.title: How science has turned HIV into a treatable, preventable condition
node.description: In just half a lifetime, modern science has turned HIV, one of the most fearsome diseases in human history, into a treatable, preventable condition.

node.title: Canberra gynaecologist facing nine patient complaints promises to have surgeries supervised
node.description: The Canberra gynaecologist at the centre of an ABC investigation has stopped working at one hospital, and has promised he will no longer perform laparoscopic surgery at another without a senior clinician present.

node.title: Woman with COVID-19 isolating in Hobart after arriving on Sydney flight
node.description: People who were on a Jetstar flight from Sydney to Hobart on Monday are asked to isolate after a passenger tests positive for COVID-19.

node.title: Appeals court judges skeptical of Trump's executive privilege claims
node.description: The judges heard arguments in a legal standoff that could ultimately reach the Supreme Court.

node.title: The Horrors of Irish Magdalene Laundries, Revisited
node.description: Claire Keegan’s “Small Things Like These” uncovers the Catholic Church’s centuries-long conspiracy to imprison, abuse and even murder “fallen women” and their children.

node.title: 14-Year-Old Shot 18 Times While Waiting for Bus After School
node.description: Authorities identified the boy as Samir Jefferson, the latest victim among the hundreds of homicides in Philadelphia since the beginning of the year.

node.title: After 10 attempts, woman says securing MIQ spot 'huge waste of time'
node.description: Some people wanting to return have been left out in the cold after the Omicron variant of Covid-19 prompted a last-minute change to the number of MIQ rooms released today.

node.title: El Chapo's wife sentenced to 3 years for helping drug cartel
node.description: Emma Coronel Aispuro previously pleaded guilty to helping her husband run his multibillion-dollar criminal empire.

node.title: U.S. warns renewed Russian aggression in Ukraine will have consequences
node.description: The U.S. and other officials have been sounding the alarm over Russia amassing troops near its border with Ukraine.

node.title: Sheriff reveals more on FedEx packages dumped in ravine
node.description: Driver made at least six trips to remote area in Blount County, Alabama, to discard products headed to 450 people.

node.title: Robert Battle on Running Ailey: ‘This Is My Choreography Now’
node.description: Celebrating 10 years as the artistic director of Alvin Ailey American Dance Theater, Battle says he is most proud of the chances he has taken.

node.title: Jim Warren, Early Influencer in Personal Computing, Dies at 85
node.description: He personified the blend of technical enthusiasm and counterculture values that shaped the industry, launching the West Coast Computer Faire in the 1970s.

node.title: Putin May 'Expand' Work Abroad with China's Xi as Russia Slams U.S. Moves in Asia
node.description: Russian President Vladimir Putin and Prime Minister Mikhail Mishustin touted common "principles" between their nation and China when it comes to global affairs.

node.title: Trump, Clinton Among Famous Flyers, No Sex Acts Seen on Jeffrey Epstein's Jet, Pilot Says
node.description: Jeffrey Epstein's pilot of nearly 30 years testified at Ghislaine Maxwell's trial that he never saw sex acts or unaccompanied children on any of his flights.

node.title: Susan Neill-Fraser's second appeal against her murder conviction has been dismissed. What comes next?
node.description: Susan Neill-Fraser's second appeal against her murder conviction has failed —  but it's the dissenting opinion of one justice that could provide a pathway for her case to reach the High Court, writes Loretta Lohberger.

node.title: Laura was meant to meet her Australian granddaughter this week — but travel rules changed mid-flight
node.description: A South African grandmother and other passengers were placed into hotel quarantine when they arrived in Australia, after the government introduced a travel ban against nine African countries while their plane was mid-flight.

node.title: How do you say ‘Omicron’?
node.description: Unlike Alpha, Beta and Delta, the name of the latest known variant is not as straightforward, with some English speakers offering up diverse pronunciations.

node.title: FDA Panel to Review Merck's COVID Pill, Question Use in Pregnant Women, Vaxxed Patients
node.description: The FDA's new panel will analyze claims that Merck's pill is less effective than promised and could cause birth defects in pregnant women.

node.title: Dr. Oz Planning to Run for U.S. Senate Seat in Pennsylvania as Republican: Associates
node.description: Oz is expected to officially announce his plans to run Tuesday night on Fox News.
